                <note rend="inline" type="source">211.31/33</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Venezuela</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cook</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-10-18">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 18, 1923</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 820</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department acknowledges the receipt of your
                    despatch No. 487 of September 27, 1923, concerning the Instrument of
                    Ratification by the Venezuelan Government of the Extradition Treaty recently
                    concluded between the United States and Venezuela, and the additional article
                    thereto.</p>
                <p>The Department accepts the suggestion made by Venezuela as indicated in the
                    memorandum enclosed with your despatch No. 417 of July 18, that the English text
                    of the Instrument of Ratification by Venezuela following the Spanish text may be
                    copied and certified to by the Minister of Foreign Affairs.</p>
                <p>You are instructed, therefore, to recall this matter to the attention of the
                    Foreign Office with a view to securing the English text of the Instrument of
                    Ratification by Venezuela appropriately certified as indicated in the memorandum
                    referred to above.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>For the Secretary of State:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">William Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
